===Fluorescent Lighting===
[[Image:leons_005.jpg|thumb|right|140px|'''Figure 4.'''<br />New two lamp T8 fixtures used in office.(Photo by Charles Swanson)]]

New Fluorescent Lamp Ballast Energy Conservation Standards ([http://ecfr.gpoaccess.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfr430_main_02.tpl 10 CFR, Part 430]) were set in 2000 by the US Department of Energy, establishing a new minimum [http://www.websters-online-dictionary.org/Ba/Ballast%20Efficacy%20Factor.html Ballast Efficacy Factor]. These new standards effectively discontinued production and sale of the ballasts used in conjunction with T12 lamps by 2005.<ref>DiLouie,Craig.(2005, November) ''Energy Policy Act of 2005 sets New Ballast Efficiency Standards.'' Retrieved November, 2009 from Lighting Controls Association website. 
http://www.aboutlightingcontrols.org/education/papers/ballast_law.shtml
</ref>  
The 40 watt T12 lamp ballasts were replaced by 36 watt T8 lamp ballasts, producing the same amount of light while using less electricity.<ref>Phillips, Ian.(n.d.) ''Fluorescent Lamps and Ballasts''. Retrieved November, 2009 from Fluorescent Lamps and Ballasts by Ian Phillips.
http://wood.bigelowsite.com/articles/fluorescent_lamps_and_ballasts.htm#Differences%20between%20T8%20and%20T12%20lamps
</ref> The T8 electronic lamp ballasts, installed by the RCEA, and certified by the [http://www.aboutlightingcontrols.org/education/papers/2008_nemaballasts.shtml National Electrical Manufacturers Association],  reduced consumption by an additional two to five watts.<ref>DiLouie,Craig.(May, 2008) ''NEMA Premium Brand Now Includes High-Efficiency Fluorescent Electronic Ballasts for 4-ft T8 Lamps''. Retrieved December, 2009 from Lighting Controls Association website.
http://www.aboutlightingcontrols.org/education/papers/2008_nemaballasts.shtml</ref> 
Older magnetic ballasted fixtures have a noticeable [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluorescent_lamp#Flicker_problems flicker] that can reduce efficiency of the lamp by up to ten percent.<ref>Fluorescent Lamp:''Ballast''.(n.d.) In ''Wikipedia''. Retrieved December, 2009
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluorescent_lamp#Ballast
</ref>
[[Image:leons_003.jpg|thumb|left|120px|'''Figure 5.'''<br />Vending machine Energy Miser.<br />(Photo by Charles Swanson)]]
All of the existing two lamp fluorescent fixtures in the shop and office (Figure 4) were replaced by the RCEA during the first phase of the retrofit.  Thirty-one electronic and nine magnetic T12 ballasted fixtures were replaced with T8 ballasted fixtures at this time.  During the final phase of the retrofit, Leon's replaced 32 400 watt HID metal halide lamps (Figure 2)<ref>Farmtek. ValuTek 400W Metal Halide Bay Light. Retrieved November, 2009.
http://www.farmtek.com/farm/supplies/prod1%3Bft1_lighting_fixtures_bulbs-ft1_metal_halide_bay_fixtures%3Bpg105713.html
